{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-awesome-readme-js","path":"/analyticalmonk/awesome-neuroscience/readme","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Track Awesome List"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"360a4259-fc54-5f33-9251-f9c43fb01262","html":"<!-- ![Awesome Neuroscience](./AWESOME2.png) --><html><head></head><body>\n<img src=\"https://github.com/analyticalmonk/awesome-neuroscience/raw/master/AWESOME2.png\" width=\"50%\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>Curated list of awesome neuroscience libraries, software and any content related to the domain.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Neuroscience\">Neuroscience</a> is the study of how the nervous system develops, its structure, and what it does. Neuroscientists focus on the brain and its impact on behavior and cognitive functions. Traditionally, neuroscience has been seen as a branch of biology, but it has grown to encompass a wide range of interdisciplinary fields that work together toward elucidating brain function at multiple levels of investigation.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/sindresorhus/awesome\"><img src=\"https://cdn.rawgit.com/sindresorhus/awesome/d7305f38d29fed78fa85652e3a63e154dd8e8829/media/badge.svg\" alt=\"Awesome\"></a></p>\n<h2 id=\"contents\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#contents\" aria-label=\"contents permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Contents</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#programming\">Programming</a>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#python\">Python</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#matlab\">Matlab</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#c\">C++</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#javascript\">JavaScript</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><a href=\"#resources\">Resources</a>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#ebooks\">Ebooks</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#blogs\">Blogs</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#moocs\">MOOCs</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#communities\">Communities</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#newsletters\">Newsletters</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#miscellaneous\">Miscellaneous</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"programming\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#programming\" aria-label=\"programming permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Programming</h2>\n<p>Software, libraries and frameworks for development purposes.</p>\n<h3 id=\"python\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#python\" aria-label=\"python permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Python</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/nengo/nengo\">Nengo</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/nengo/nengo\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">714</span></span></a> - Library for creating and simulating large-scale brain models.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/nipy/nitime\">Nitime</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/nipy/nitime\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">210</span></span></a> - Timeseries analysis for neuroscience data.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/nilearn/nilearn\">Nilearn</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/nilearn/nilearn\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">894</span></span></a> - Module for performing statistical learning/machine learning on NeuroImaging data.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/nipy/dipy\">DIPY</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/nipy/dipy\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">547</span></span></a> - Toolbox for analysis of MR diffusion imaging.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/mne-tools/mne-python\">MNE-Python</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/mne-tools/mne-python\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">2k</span></span></a> - Community-driven software for processing time-resolved neural signals including electroencephalography (EEG) and magnetoencephalography (MEG).</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/nipy/nibabel\">NiBabel</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/nipy/nibabel\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">500</span></span></a> - Provides read and write access to some common medical and neuroimaging file formats.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/psychopy/psychopy\">PsychoPy</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/psychopy/psychopy\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">1.3k</span></span></a> - Package for running psychology and neuroscience experiments. It allows for creating psychology stimuli in Python.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/numenta/nupic\">NuPic</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/numenta/nupic\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">6.3k</span></span></a> - Numenta Platform for Intelligent Computing is an implementation of Hierarchical Temporal Memory (HTM), a theory of intelligence based strictly on the neuroscience of the neocortex.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/brian-team/brian2\">Brian2</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/brian-team/brian2\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">696</span></span></a> - Free, open source simulator for spiking neural networks.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/expyriment/expyriment\">expyriment</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/expyriment/expyriment\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">102</span></span></a> - Platform-independent lightweight Python library for designing and conducting timing-critical behavioural and neuroimaging experiments.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/Hananel-Hazan/bindsnet\">BindsNET</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/Hananel-Hazan/bindsnet\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">1.1k</span></span></a> - Package for simulating spiking neural networks for reinforcement &#x26; machine learning.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/SpikeInterface/spikeinterface\">SpikeInterface</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/SpikeInterface/spikeinterface\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">136</span></span></a> - Framework designed to unify spike-sorting technologies</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"matlab\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#matlab\" aria-label=\"matlab permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Matlab</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://bdtoolbox.org/\">Brain Dynamics Toolbox</a> - Open software for simulating dynamical systems in neuroscience.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://neuroimage.usc.edu/brainstorm/\">BrainStorm</a> - Open-source application dedicated to the analysis of brain recordings (MEG, EEG, fNIRS, ECoG, depth electrodes and multiunit electrophysiology).</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://sccn.ucsd.edu/eeglab/\">EEGLAB</a> - Interactive Matlab toolbox for processing continuous and event-related EEG, MEG and other electrophysiological data.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/fieldtrip/fieldtrip\">FieldTrip</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/fieldtrip/fieldtrip\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">658</span></span></a> - Toolbox for MEG and EEG analysis.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://psychtoolbox.org/\">Psychtoolbox-3</a> -  Free set of Matlab and GNU Octave functions for vision and neuroscience research.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.fil.ion.ucl.ac.uk/spm/\">SPM</a> - Free and open source software for the  analysis of brain imaging data sequences (fMRI, PET, SPECT, EEG, MEG).</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"c\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#c\" aria-label=\"c permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>C++</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/BlueBrain/Brayns\">Brayns</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/BlueBrain/Brayns\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">269</span></span></a> - Minimalistic visualiser that can perform ray-traced rendering of neurons. Ray-tracing can help to highlight areas of neural circuits where cells touch each other and where synapses are being created leading to a better understanding of how individual cells and subsequently the brain functions.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"javascript\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#javascript\" aria-label=\"javascript permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>JavaScript</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/aces/brainbrowser\">Brainbrowser</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/aces/brainbrowser\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">310</span></span></a> - Library exposing set of web-based 3D visualization tools primarily targetting neuroimaging.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.jspsych.org/\">jsPsych</a> - Library for creating and running behavioural experiments in a web browser.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"r\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#r\" aria-label=\"r permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>R</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/jefferis/nat\">nat: NeuroAnatomy Toolbox</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/jefferis/nat\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">58</span></span></a> - Package for the (3D) visualisation and analysis of biological image data, especially tracings of single neurons.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/cwatson/brainGraph\">brainGraph</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/cwatson/brainGraph\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">131</span></span></a> - Package for performing graph theory analyses of brain MRI data.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"resources\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#resources\" aria-label=\"resources permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Resources</h2>\n<p>Interesting resources related to neuroscience.</p>\n<h3 id=\"ebooks\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#ebooks\" aria-label=\"ebooks permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Ebooks</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://nba.uth.tmc.edu/neuroscience/m/index.htm\">Neuroscience Online</a> - Open-access electronic textbook and interactive courseware covering neuroscience in depth. Provided by the Department of Neurobiology and Anantomy at the University of Texas Medical School at Houston.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://grey.colorado.edu/CompCogNeuro/index.php/CCNBook/Main\">Computational Cognitive Neuroscience</a> - Text which provides an in-depth introduction to the main ideas in the computational cognitive neuroscience, a field which aims to understand the brain by using biologically based computational models.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://neuronaldynamics.epfl.ch\">Neuronal Dynamics</a> - Open-access electronic textbook that covers computational and theoretical neuroscience. Provided by École Polytechnique Fédérale de Lausanne (EPFL).</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"blogs\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#blogs\" aria-label=\"blogs permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Blogs</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.discovermagazine.com/author/neuroskeptic\">Neuroskeptic</a> - <a href=\"http://discovermagazine.com/\">Discover magazine</a>'s neuroscience blog which offers a look at the latest developments in neuroscience, psychiatry and psychology through a critical lens.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://neurocritic.blogspot.in/\">The Neurocritic</a> - Often critical takes on the most sensationalistic recent findings in Human Brain Imaging, Cognitive Neuroscience, and Psychopharmacology.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://blogs.scientificamerican.com/scicurious-brain/\">The scicurious brain</a> - Maintained by <a href=\"https://blogs.scientificamerican.com/\">Scientific American</a>, this blog typically covers one research paper in a single entry.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://blogs.nature.com/actionpotential\">Action Potential</a> - Forum operated by neuroscience editors at the journal, Nature.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"moocs\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#moocs\" aria-label=\"moocs permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>MOOCs</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Massive_open_online_course\">Massive Open Online Courses (MOOCs)</a> are free Web-based distance learning programs that are designed for the participation of large numbers of geographically dispersed students.\nMOOCs may be patterned on a college or university course or may be less structured.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.mcb80x.org/\">The Fundamentals of Neuroscience | Harvard &#x26; edX</a> - Serves an introductory survery of topics in neuroscience and has no specific prerequisites, though some prior exposure to biology and/or chemistry can be helpful.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://ocw.mit.edu/courses/brain-and-cognitive-sciences/9-01-introduction-to-neuroscience-fall-2007/\">Introduction to Neuroscience | MIT OCW</a> - Introduction to the mammalian nervous system, with emphasis on the structure and function of the human brain.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.coursera.org/learn/computational-neuroscience\">Computational Neuroscience | Coursera</a> - Provides an introduction to basic computational methods for understanding what nervous systems do and for determining how they function.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.coursera.org/learn/medical-neuroscience\">Medical Neuroscience</a> - Explores the functional organization and neurophysiology of the human central nervous system, while providing a neurobiological framework for understanding human behavior.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/NeuromatchAcademy/course-content\">Neuromatch Academy</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/NeuromatchAcademy/course-content\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">2.3k</span></span></a> - Jupyter notebooks for the three-week intensive summer school in computational neuroscience.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"communities\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#communities\" aria-label=\"communities permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Communities</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.quora.com/topic/Neuroscience-1\">Quora</a> - Neuroscience topic on Quora contains answers, often by experts, to questions ranging from basic to advanced.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/ScienceNetwork/comments/ptye0/link_tables/\">Reddit</a> - List of neuroscience, psychology and cognitive science subreddits.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://psychology.stackexchange.com\">StackExchange</a> - Psychology and neuroscience StackExchange site.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"newsletters\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#newsletters\" aria-label=\"newsletters permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Newsletters</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://neuro.hms.harvard.edu/harvard-mahoney-neuroscience-institute/hmni-newsletter\">On The Brain</a> - Harvard Mahoney Neuroscience Institute's quarterly e-newsletter.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.tnb.ua.ac.be/mailman/listinfo/comp-neuro\">Comp-neuro</a> - A mailing list that is is intended to address the broad range of research approaches and issues involved in the general field of computational neuroscience.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.brainpost.co/\">BrainPost</a> - A mailing list that delivers weekly easy-to-read summaries of the latest neuroscience publications.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"miscellaneous\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#miscellaneous\" aria-label=\"miscellaneous permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Miscellaneous</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/awesomedata/awesome-public-datasets#neuroscience\">Awesome Public Datasets - Neuroscience</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/awesomedata/awesome-public-datasets#neuroscience\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">51.4k</span></span></a> - High-quality open neuroscience datasets.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://justinmeiners.github.io/neural-nets-sim/\">McCulloch &#x26; Pitts Neural Net Simulator</a> - Simulator for a historical computational model based on neurons.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://senselab.med.yale.edu/ModelDB/default.cshtml\">ModelDB</a> - Searchable database for computational neuroscience models.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://senselab.med.yale.edu/NeuronDB\">NeuronDB</a> - Searchable database for  of three types of neuronal properties: voltage gated conductances, neurotransmitter receptors, and neurotransmitter substances.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://neuroelectro.org/\">NeuroElectro</a> - Searchable database of neurons and their electrophysiological properties (extracted from literature)</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://learn-anything.xyz/neuroscience\">Neuroscience Mindmap</a> - Interactive mindmap containing curated resources for anyone interested in learning neuroscience.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/PhABC/neuroSummerSchools\">neuroSummerSchools</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/PhABC/neuroSummerSchools\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">190</span></span></a> - List of summer (and seasonal) summer schools in neuroscience and related fields.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://brainpodcast.com/\">Brain Matters</a> - Neuroscience podcast where real neuroscientists sit down and talk about the brain.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"contribute\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#contribute\" aria-label=\"contribute permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Contribute</h2>\n<p>Contributions welcome! Read the <a href=\"https://github.com/analyticalmonk/awesome-neuroscience/blob/master/contributing.md\">contribution guidelines</a> first.</p>\n<h2 id=\"license\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#license\" aria-label=\"license permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>License</h2>\n<p><a href=\"http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0\"><img src=\"http://mirrors.creativecommons.org/presskit/buttons/88x31/svg/cc-zero.svg\" alt=\"CC0\"></a></p>\n<p>To the extent possible under law, <a href=\"https://github.com/analyticalmonk\">Akash Tandon</a> has waived all copyright and\nrelated or neighboring rights to this work.</p>","tableOfContents":"<ul>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#contents\">Contents</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#programming\">Programming</a></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#python\">Python</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#matlab\">Matlab</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#c\">C++</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#javascript\">JavaScript</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#r\">R</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#resources\">Resources</a></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#ebooks\">Ebooks</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#blogs\">Blogs</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#moocs\">MOOCs</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#communities\">Communities</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#newsletters\">Newsletters</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#miscellaneous\">Miscellaneous</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#contribute\">Contribute</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#license\">License</a></p>\n</li>\n</ul>","headings":[{"id":"contents","value":"Contents","depth":2},{"id":"programming","value":"Programming","depth":2},{"id":"python","value":"Python","depth":3},{"id":"matlab","value":"Matlab","depth":3},{"id":"c","value":"C++","depth":3},{"id":"javascript","value":"JavaScript","depth":3},{"id":"r","value":"R","depth":3},{"id":"resources","value":"Resources","depth":2},{"id":"ebooks","value":"Ebooks","depth":3},{"id":"blogs","value":"Blogs","depth":3},{"id":"moocs","value":"MOOCs","depth":3},{"id":"communities","value":"Communities","depth":3},{"id":"newsletters","value":"Newsletters","depth":3},{"id":"miscellaneous","value":"Miscellaneous","depth":3},{"id":"contribute","value":"Contribute","depth":2},{"id":"license","value":"License","depth":2}]},"awesomeListMeta":{"readmeParsedAt":"2022-10-14T05:08:42.862Z","repo":"analyticalmonk/awesome-neuroscience","description":"A curated list of awesome neuroscience libraries, software and any content related to the domain.","readmeItemsUpdatedTime":1635685540000,"descriptionHTML":"<div>A curated list of awesome neuroscience libraries, software and any content related to the domain.</div>","stargazerCount":946,"category":"Health and Social Science"},"previous":{"id":"34725494-8a85-52bb-b14c-3514c8ee3982","fields":{"repo":"dreamingechoes/awesome-mental-health","slug":"/dreamingechoes/awesome-mental-health/readme"}},"next":{"id":"e868d9fa-3890-5b65-9ef9-75082bc30732","fields":{"repo":"danvoyce/awesome-creative-tech-events","slug":"/danvoyce/awesome-creative-tech-events/readme"}}},"pageContext":{"repo":"analyticalmonk/awesome-neuroscience","id":"360a4259-fc54-5f33-9251-f9c43fb01262","previousId":"34725494-8a85-52bb-b14c-3514c8ee3982","nextId":"e868d9fa-3890-5b65-9ef9-75082bc30732"}},"staticQueryHashes":["228695001","2744905544","2828988102"]}